== Donations received ==
Following the success of the film &quot;Black Panther&quot;, in 2018 Disney donated $1million to Boys &amp; Girls Clubs of America for the development of STEM programs in the United States. The donation was to be allocated to help grow the group&#x27;s national STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics) curriculum. According to Mimi LeClair, president and CEO of Boys and Girls Clubs of Chicago, it is very important for young people to have a solid background in STEM to compete in the global economy.

